===========================================================================
                      xportlet proxymanager bugs
===========================================================================

-------------------------
Customizing Proxy Manager
-------------------------

  After pressing the 'Customize' button to commit a user's default parameter
  changes, the portlet maximizes and returns to the main screen.  If you 
  then click the 'Get Proxy' button, your old defaults will be loaded.  But
  if you return the portlet to normal size, the changed defaults will be
  displayed.  So, either

  1) The modified default parameters are saved to disk but cached default
     parameters are not updated,

   or

  2) The default parameters are not saved to disk until the the portlet is
     returned to normal or the user logs out

  Suspect (1) but haven't figured out cause yet.

  Work around: return portlet to normal size immediately after pressing
                   the 'Customize' button.
